.TH "devm_kstrdup" 9 "devm_kstrdup" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_kstrdup \- Allocate resource managed space and copy an existing string into that.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "char *" devm_kstrdup
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "const char *s "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Device to allocate memory for
.IP "s" 12
the string to duplicate
.IP "gfp" 12
the GFP mask used in the \fBdevm_kmalloc\fP call when
allocating memory
.SH "RETURN"
Pointer to allocated string on success, NULL on failure.
